This provides you with an overview of the existing serial numbers in your warehouse. - **C - Serial Number Requirement on Stock Level** You use this serial number requirement to store the exact storage bin information for a serial number. - **No Serial Number Requirement** You use this serial number requirement to store serial numbers in processes or to cancel the serial number requirement in a specific warehouse number. # Example

Documentation.LongDescription: # Definition Specifies the packaging material (for example, a crate, a wooden pallet, a container), that can be used to package and transport goods. The data for the packaging material is stored in the product master record. # Use If you enter a packaging material for a handling unit, the system automatically proposes data such as the allowed weight and volume from the relevant product master record.

# Definition Specifies the total of the tare weight of the handling unit and its loading weight. # Example Your packaging material has a gross weight of 0.5 kg and a 'maximum weight' of 2 kg. You pack product 'spark plugs' in the packaging material. The maximum number of spark plugs you can pack in the packaging material is 4 (each gross weight 500 g). The loading weight of the HU is therefore 2 kg. The tare weight of the HU is the packaging material weight (0.5 kg) plus the weight of the auxiliary packaging material (0.1 kg). The total weight of the HU is your loading weight, which is 2 kg, plus your tare weight of 0.6 kg, giving a total weight of 2.6 kg.

# Definition Specifies the total of the tare weight of the handling unit and its loading weight. # Example Your packaging material has a gross weight of 0.5 kg and a 'maximum weight' of 2 kg. You pack product 'spark plugs' in the packaging material. The maximum number of spark plugs you can pack in the packaging material is 4 (each gross weight 500 g). The loading weight of the HU is therefore 2 kg. The tare weight of the HU is the packaging material weight (0.5 kg) plus the weight of the auxiliary packaging material (0.1 kg). The total weight of the HU is your loading weight, which is 2 kg, plus your tare weight of 0.6 kg, giving a total weight of 2.6 kg.

Documentation.LongDescription: # Definition Unit of measure that you can use to enter quantities as an alternative to the **base unit of measure**.

# Definition Specifies the partner or organization that owns the stock. Usually this is a plant. For vendor consignment stocks, the vendor is the stock owner. # Use Each stock quantity must always be assigned to an owner. This enables you to manage your own stock as well as vendor consignment stock of the same material. # Example For your own stock, the plant is both the owner and the party entitled to dispose of the stock. For vendor consignment stock, the vendor is the owner and the plant is the party entitled to dispose of the stock.
# Definition Alphanumeric key uniquely identifying the **material**.

# Definition Text containing up to 40 characters that describes the **material** in more detail. # Use You can enter one material description in each of any number of languages. # Procedure In principle, you enter the material description on the data screen of the first user department for which you enter data, and in your logon language. You can overwrite the material description on the Basic Data screen. # Dependencies

The total weight of the HU is your loading weight, which is 2 kg, plus your tare weight of 0.6 kg, giving a total weight of 2.6 kg.

# Definition Breakdown of a complex physical warehouse. Storage types differ in their storage techniques, their organizational form, or their function. A warehouse can be made up of the following storage types, for example: - Goods receipt area - Picking area - High rack storage area - Bulk storage - General storage area - Goods issue area # Example

# Definition The **storage section** is a logical or physical subdivision of a **storage type**. Each section can summarize an array of storage bins. You can specify the criteria for this to suit your requirements, for example, **fast-moving items** or **slow-moving items**. # Example

Property.sap:quickinfo: Number of Handling Units in Storage Bin

Documentation.LongDescription: # Definition In a bulk storage area, this is the number of handling units in the storage bin. # Use This field is updated automatically during stock placement and stock removal.

# Definition Specifies the section of the storage bin. # Use In stock placement strategy "Pallet Storage (According to HU Type)", the section decides which handling unit (HU) type and how many HUs of this type can be placed into storage. The sectioning is determined dynamically in the storage bin by the first storage unit placed in the bin. The sectioning is deleted as soon as the last storage unit has been removed from the storage bin.
# Definition Means that the ** storage bin** will be blocked for stock removals. # Procedure You can set this indicator manually.

# Definition Specifies the total maximum weight allowed in the storage bin without affecting the stability of the shelving or rack assembly frames. # Use During putaway, the system calculates the difference between the maximum weight allowed and the weight already in the storage bin. If the weight of the product to be put away into the storage bin is greater than the remaining capacity, the product cannot be put away into this storage bin. # Procedure Enter the maximum weight allowed for the storage bin. You can switch this capacity check on and off, as required.

Property.Name: Weight
Property.sap:label: Weight Used
Property.sap:quickinfo: Weight of Materials in Storage Bin

Documentation.LongDescription: # Definition Current total weight of products in the storage bin. # Use The total weight is used to check the weight capacity in connection with the maximum load capacity of a bin. # Procedure The system calculates this value by adding together the individual total weights of all the products in the storage bin.

# Use **In packaging material** The volume up to which other products can be packed into the packaging material. **In storage bin type** The maximum volume allowed for bins in this storage type. # Example
# Use The volume unit is used, for example, for the maximum allowed volume and the volume of products in storage bins. # Example

# Definition In this field, you define the maximum capacity for the storage bin, either in the master data for the storage bin or in the Customizing for the storage bin type. You define the capacity consumption for a product or for the packaging material for a handling unit in the material master. If you have selected a capacity check method for the storage bin’s storage type, the total capacity consumption for a quantity of the product or the number of handling units is compared against the maximum capacity for the storage bin to determine if the product or handling units will fit in the storage bin.

# Definition The system updates and displays the remaining available capacity of the **storage bin** in this data field. This is calculated by subtracting the bin’s capacity utilization from the total capacity.
